@JLimperg, do you think it makes sense for Aesop to throw an error if an `apply` attribute is applied to an `Iff` lemma ?
I wondered this exact question too - it's just about feasible that applying an `iff` lemma is the right thing to do in certain cases. It seems unlikely, but makes me hesitant to give an error

> @JLimperg, do you think it makes sense for Aesop to throw an error if an `apply` attribute is applied to an `Iff` lemma ?

I'll implement a warning, with an option to disable it. Indeed it seems unlikely (but possible) that an `Iff` lemma would make a useful `apply` rule.
